    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Emission spectroscopy technique used to determine elemental content of materials. The material is heated to a high temperature causing the electrons in the sample to emit light which is converted into a spectral pattern. In the broader sense, optical emission spectroscopy includes ICP optical emission spectrometry, which uses an inductively coupled plasma as the excitation source.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
